article.description: Chancellor Barnard had 18 points on 7-of-11 shooting and J.C. Show hit a 3-pointer as time expired as Binghamton beat LIU Brooklyn 68-67 on Friday at the Barclays Center to snap a four-game skid.
article.headline: Show's 3 at the buzzer lifts Binghamton over LIU Brooklyn
article.linkText: Show's 3 at the buzzer lifts Binghamton over LIU Brooklyn
article.story: NEW YORK -- Chancellor Barnard had 18 points on 7-of-11 shooting and J.C. Show hit a 3-pointer as time expired as Binghamton beat LIU Brooklyn 68-67 on Friday at the Barclays Center to snap a four-game skid. Show shot just 4 of 13 from the field but finished with 15 points and three steals. Everson Davis scored 13 and Sam Sessoms had 11 points and six assists for Binghamton (4-9). Show hit a 3 with 41 seconds left and, after Julian Batts made a jumper for LIU Brooklyn, Davis' tipin trimmed the Bearcats' deficit to 66-64 with six seconds to go. Jashaun Agosto made 1 of 2 free throws to make it a three-point game before Batts fouled Show with two seconds remaining. He hit the first free throw and intentionally missed the second, which went out of bounds off the Blackbirds. Show came around a screen by Caleb Stewart, took the inbound pass from Sessoms in the right corner and drilled the winner. Ty Flowers had 27 points and grabbed 11 rebounds -- both career highs -- for LIU Brooklyn (5-6). Davis hit a jumper with 18:35 left in the first half to make it 2-0 but Flowers hit a 3-pointer 21 seconds later and Binghamton trailed until Show's winner.
